   The year is 1887.

17:21.040 --> 17:22.675
Now this is
a chart of the distance

17:22.709 --> 17:25.244
  the average farmer was
  from his nearest neighbor.

17:25.278 --> 17:27.681
  Now in some cases,
  hundreds of miles.

17:27.714 --> 17:30.950
 Now it can take weeks
 for a letter to travel
 from one place to another...

17:31.051 --> 17:35.355
 Pace yourself, Nikki.
 You don't wanna peak too soon.

17:35.388 --> 17:38.725
  And,
  what if you have an emergency
  and you need a doctor?

17:38.758 --> 17:41.695
   The answer is, my invention.
   The telephone.

17:41.728 --> 17:43.663
-Our invention.
-Right.

17:44.330 --> 17:46.433
  Okay, here's how it works.

17:46.466 --> 17:50.070
   You dial a number on your
   phone and someone
   else's phone rings.

17:50.070 --> 17:52.339
 They answer, you talk.
 It's all in seconds.

17:52.372 --> 17:55.408
   Well I'm sold, does
   this thing come in beige?

17:55.442 --> 17:58.945
This telephone of yours.
How much does it cost?

17:59.913 --> 18:01.848
   Well, it costs about $45.

18:02.649 --> 18:04.851
 I can buy two cows for that.

18:04.884 --> 18:06.619
   Can I get milk
   from your phone?

18:06.653 --> 18:09.122
Well if you call the dairy,
you can.

18:10.023 --> 18:12.025
   I don't think so.

18:12.058 --> 18:14.894
   I'm just a poor farmer,
   I got a lot of
   chores and plowing to do.

18:14.928 --> 18:18.131
 Unless you can change my mind,
 I'm not interested.

18:19.366 --> 18:21.034
   Ring, ring, ring.

18:21.034 --> 18:23.103
  Come on, Zack.
  Aren't things
  bad enough already?

18:23.136 --> 18:25.038
 Can somebody
 answer that, please?

18:29.042 --> 18:32.045
  -Hello.
  -Yeah, hi, is Nikki around?

18:32.045 --> 18:34.347
Tell him I'm not here.

18:34.381 --> 18:37.050
  I think you
  should talk to him.

18:37.083 --> 18:38.318
   ( sighs )

18:38.351 --> 18:40.453
 Hello, hello.

18:40.487 --> 18:42.822
 Look, I know you're there.
 I can hear your
 teeth grinding.

18:42.856 --> 18:45.792
 -What do you want?
 -You never answered my letter.

18:45.825 --> 18:47.060
  Aren't we friends anymore?

18:47.060 --> 18:49.863
 -I think I'm about
 to invent the hang up.
 -What's that?

18:49.896 --> 18:53.700
  You never received my letter?
  Must have gotten lost.

18:53.733 --> 18:56.770
 I'm sure glad I called
 you on the telephone.

18:56.803 --> 18:59.806
  Yeah. Right the telephone.

18:59.839 --> 19:02.909
 -It's a good thing I have one.
 -Right.

19:03.009 --> 19:07.280
 It might cost more, but thanks
 to the phone friends can talk
 things out. Right?

19:09.249 --> 19:12.452
I mean we were friends
since the first grade.

19:12.485 --> 19:15.689
We used to play
little league together,
remember?

19:15.722 --> 19:17.857
 We had a lot of fun!

19:17.891 --> 19:20.026
  Yeah, I know what you mean.

19:21.394 --> 19:25.065
-Well I'm really
glad you called.
-I'm glad I called too.

19:28.768 --> 19:32.839
  So, if not for the phone,
  your friendship
  might have ended.

19:32.872 --> 19:36.142
   Right.
   Instead I think it's
   a little bit better now.

19:37.277 --> 19:40.280
I don't know. I'm still
bothered by one thing.

19:41.448 --> 19:44.184
   This invention of yours,

19:44.217 --> 19:46.953
  can I get a mobile
  phone for my horse?

19:48.421 --> 19:51.091
 Well done both of you.
 A-minus.

19:53.526 --> 19:58.365
-Hey,
thanks for bailing us out.
-What are partners for?

19:58.398 --> 20:00.467
   After school,
   you wanna throw
   the ball around?

20:00.500 --> 20:02.836
 I don't know. I'll call you.

